lucentPM4MibRev.name: lucentPM4MibRev
lucentPM4MibRev.description: This object specifies the current MIB revision number. Example of the MIB revision can be PM4xxx for PM4 product and PM3xxx for PM3 products etc. Where xxx can be any combination of alpha-numeric characters.

lucentPM4SWRev.name: lucentPM4SWRev
lucentPM4SWRev.description: This object specifies the ComOS revision number. Example of the ComOS revision can be ComOS4.xx. Where xxx can be any combination of alpha-numeric characters.

lucentPM4ChasSummary.name: lucentPM4ChasSummary
lucentPM4ChasSummary.description: This object provides general information about the PortMaster 4 chassis operational status. This object is read-only. The DisplayString represents a summary of all the devices in the chassis as follows: Bytes 1 - 2 '0''0' Byte 3 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 4 space Bytes 5 - 6 '0''1' Byte 7 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 8 space Bytes 9 - 10 '0''2' Byte 11 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 12 space Bytes 13 - 14 '0''3' Byte 15 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 16 space Bytes 17 - 18 '0''4' Byte 19 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 20 space Bytes 21 - 22 '0''5' Byte 23 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 24 space Bytes 25 - 26 '0''6' Byte 27 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 28 space Bytes 29 - 30 '0''7' Byte 31 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 32 space Bytes 33 - 34 '0''8' Byte 35 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 36 space Bytes 37 - 38 '0''9' Byte 39 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 40 space Bytes 41 - 42 '1''0' Byte 43 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 44 space Bytes 45 - 46 '1''1' Byte 47 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 48 space Bytes 49 - 50 '1''2' Byte 51 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 52 space Bytes 53 - 54 '1''3' Byte 55 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 56 space Bytes 57 - 58 '1''4' Byte 59 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 60 space Bytes 61 - 62 '1''5' Byte 63 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 64 space Bytes 65 - 66 'P''1' Byte 67 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 68 space Bytes 69 - 70 'P''2' Byte 71 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 72 space Bytes 73 - 74 'P''3' Byte 75 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 76 space Bytes 77 - 78 'D''1' Byte 79 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 80 space Bytes 81 - 82 'D''2' Byte 83 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 84 space Bytes 85 - 86 'F''1' Byte 87 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 88 space Bytes 89 - 90 'F''2' Byte 91 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 92 space Bytes 93 - 94 'F''3' Byte 95 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Byte 96 space Bytes 97 - 98 'F''4' Byte 99 'U', 'D', 'M', 'F', 'O' Legend '#''#' Represents the board number 'F''#' Represents the Fan # 'P''#' Represents the Power Supply # 'D''#' Represents the DC Power Supply # 'U' Up 'D' Down 'M' Maintenance 'F' Failed 'O' Other unknown state.

lucentPM4ChasCmdTable.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdTable
lucentPM4ChasCmdTable.description: Table describing the commands that can be issued to the agent to perform specific actions to any card, port or device in the system. For example to erase the flash or a particular file from the flash. Note that only a station configured with the appropriate authentication string can issue commands to the agent.

lucentPM4ChasCmdEntry.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdEntry
lucentPM4ChasCmdEntry.description: Entries in the command table for the chassis commands. This describes one entry or row in the command table.

lucentPM4ChasCmdIndex.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdIndex
lucentPM4ChasCmdIndex.description: This object specifies the index in the command table. The values for this object is limited to the size of the command table on the network element. The size of the command table is set to 10 which can be changed if and when users need to schedule more than 10 commands at a given time.

lucentPM4ChasCmdBoardId.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdBoardId
lucentPM4ChasCmdBoardId.description: This object specifies the board for which the command is to be applied. The values for this object is limited to the Max number of boards.

lucentPM4ChasCmdUnitType.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdUnitType
lucentPM4ChasCmdUnitType.description: This object specifies the type of the device to which this command must apply.

lucentPM4ChasCmdUnitIndex.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdUnitIndex
lucentPM4ChasCmdUnitIndex.description: This object specifies the interface index.

lucentPM4ChasCmdDevId.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdDevId
lucentPM4ChasCmdDevId.description: This object specifies the sub-unit id for which the command must be applied to. This value will be used by the agent to index to the correct sub-device on a board. For example, this object can have values from 1 - 96 for the modems or 1 - 4 for T1 or 1 - 3 for the E1.

lucentPM4ChasCmdId.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdId
lucentPM4ChasCmdId.description: This object specifies the command. Each command takes a unique value. The completion status of this command is set in the result object of the table.

lucentPM4ChasCmdParams.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdParams
lucentPM4ChasCmdParams.description: This object specifies the command parameters. Each parameter must be seperated by a blank space. The last parameter is terminated with a ';'.

lucentPM4ChasCmdResult.name: lucentPM4ChasCmdResult
lucentPM4ChasCmdResult.description: This object specifies the command result. The result for each of the previous 10 commands will be stored in a table, which can be retrieved by the client when needed.

lucentPM4SerialTable.name: lucentPM4SerialTable
lucentPM4SerialTable.description: A list of serial interface entries.

lucentPM4SerialEntry.name: lucentPM4SerialEntry
lucentPM4SerialEntry.description: A serial interface entry containing objects at the physical and session layer.

lucentPM4SerialBoardIndex.name: lucentPM4SerialBoardIndex
lucentPM4SerialBoardIndex.description: A unique value for each board in the PortMaster chassis. The Max value of this variable is limited by the number of boards in the chassis. This value is limited to 255.

lucentPM4SerialUnitType.name: lucentPM4SerialUnitType
lucentPM4SerialUnitType.description: Unit type indicates the serial port. The interface table ifIndex is a combination of board index, unit type and unit index.

lucentPM4SerialIndex.name: lucentPM4SerialIndex
lucentPM4SerialIndex.description: A unique value for each serial interface on a given board.

lucentPM4ModemId.name: lucentPM4ModemId
lucentPM4ModemId.description: This object is the cross reference to the modem interface table index. The value is dynamically assigned when the call is established.

lucentPM4SerialPortNumber.name: lucentPM4SerialPortNumber
lucentPM4SerialPortNumber.description: A serial port to which this modem is assigned for this call.

lucentPM4SerialPhysType.name: lucentPM4SerialPhysType
lucentPM4SerialPhysType.description: The type of physical serial interface, distinguished according to the physical/link protocol(s) being currently used on the interface. When this object is set to asyn(2), then the service types dial-in, dial- out, login, and device are valid. When this object is set to sync(3), the serial service types dial-in, dial- out and hardwired are valid.

lucentPM4SerialPortStatus.name: lucentPM4SerialPortStatus
lucentPM4SerialPortStatus.description: The status of the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialDS0State.name: lucentPM4SerialDS0State
lucentPM4SerialDS0State.description: Cross reference value for each DS0 for a given T1/E1 line and a given board in the PM4 chassis.

lucentPM4SerialUser.name: lucentPM4SerialUser
lucentPM4SerialUser.description: Name of the active user. Blank if not active.

lucentPM4SerialSessionId.name: lucentPM4SerialSessionId
lucentPM4SerialSessionId.description: A unique Session Identifier which matches the RADIUS session ID. Blank when not using RADIUS.

lucentPM4SerialTypeHardwired.name: lucentPM4SerialTypeHardwired
lucentPM4SerialTypeHardwired.description: The active type of service being provided by the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialTypeNwDialIn.name: lucentPM4SerialTypeNwDialIn
lucentPM4SerialTypeNwDialIn.description: The active type of service being provided by the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialTypeNwDialout.name: lucentPM4SerialTypeNwDialout
lucentPM4SerialTypeNwDialout.description: The active type of service being provided by the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialTypeLogin.name: lucentPM4SerialTypeLogin
lucentPM4SerialTypeLogin.description: The active type of service being provided by the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialTypeDevice.name: lucentPM4SerialTypeDevice
lucentPM4SerialTypeDevice.description: The active type of service being provided by the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialTypeDeviceName.name: lucentPM4SerialTypeDeviceName
lucentPM4SerialTypeDeviceName.description: Device name if the lucentPM4SerialTypeDevice is enabled. This is a string of characters (e.g. /dev/tty1) indicating the device name.

lucentPM4SerialDirection.name: lucentPM4SerialDirection
lucentPM4SerialDirection.description: The direction the active session was initiated.

lucentPM4SerialStarted.name: lucentPM4SerialStarted
lucentPM4SerialStarted.description: The amount of time this session has been active.

lucentPM4SerialIdle.name: lucentPM4SerialIdle
lucentPM4SerialIdle.description: The amount of time this session has been idle.

lucentPM4SerialInSpeed.name: lucentPM4SerialInSpeed
lucentPM4SerialInSpeed.description: An estimate of the serial interface's current inbound bandwidth in bits per second.

lucentPM4SerialOutSpeed.name: lucentPM4SerialOutSpeed
lucentPM4SerialOutSpeed.description: An estimate of the serial interface's current outbound bandwidth in bits per second.

lucentPM4SerialIpAddress.name: lucentPM4SerialIpAddress
lucentPM4SerialIpAddress.description: The IP address associated with the serial interface. If being used as a network type port, this is the remote user's IP address. If being used as a device or login, this is the IP address of the host the user is connected to.

lucentPM4SerialifDescr.name: lucentPM4SerialifDescr
lucentPM4SerialifDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the network interface bound to the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialInOctets.name: lucentPM4SerialInOctets
lucentPM4SerialInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialOutOctets.name: lucentPM4SerialOutOctets
lucentPM4SerialOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted on the serial interface.

lucentPM4SerialQOctets.name: lucentPM4SerialQOctets
lucentPM4SerialQOctets.description: The total number of octets queued on the serial interface.

lucentPM4T1E1Table.name: lucentPM4T1E1Table
lucentPM4T1E1Table.description: A list of T1/E1 interface entries.

lucentPM4T1E1Entry.name: lucentPM4T1E1Entry
lucentPM4T1E1Entry.description: A T1/E1 entry containing objects at the physical layer.

lucentPM4T1E1BoardIndex.name: lucentPM4T1E1BoardIndex
lucentPM4T1E1BoardIndex.description: A unique value for each board in the PM4 chassis.

lucentPM4T1E1UnitType.name: lucentPM4T1E1UnitType
lucentPM4T1E1UnitType.description: This object specifies the type of the unit as the T1/E1 line. This value is a part of the interface table ifIndex.

lucentPM4T1E1Index.name: lucentPM4T1E1Index
lucentPM4T1E1Index.description: A unique value for each T1/E1 interface.

lucentPM4T1E1SerialIndex.name: lucentPM4T1E1SerialIndex
lucentPM4T1E1SerialIndex.description: The value of the instance for the serial port. This object provides a cross reference from the T1/E1 interface to the serial port to which it is mapped.

lucentPM4T1E1SerialCount.name: lucentPM4T1E1SerialCount
lucentPM4T1E1SerialCount.description: The number of serial ports assigned to this interface. If this is a Channelized T1/E1, then the count is 24/32. If this is a fractional T1/E1, then the count can be any number between 1 and a number less than 24/32.

lucentPM4T1E1PhysType.name: lucentPM4T1E1PhysType
lucentPM4T1E1PhysType.description: The type of interface (T1 or E1).

lucentPM4T1E1Status.name: lucentPM4T1E1Status
lucentPM4T1E1Status.description: The current operational status of the interface.

lucentPM4T1E1Function.name: lucentPM4T1E1Function
lucentPM4T1E1Function.description: The configured function of the interface.

lucentPM4T1E1SuperSignal.name: lucentPM4T1E1SuperSignal
lucentPM4T1E1SuperSignal.description: The configured supervisory signalling mode for this interface.

lucentPM4T1E1StartMode.name: lucentPM4T1E1StartMode
lucentPM4T1E1StartMode.description: The configured start mode for this interface.

lucentPM4T1E1ChangeTime.name: lucentPM4T1E1ChangeTime
lucentPM4T1E1ChangeTime.description: The amount of time since the last status change.

lucentPM4T1E1RecvLevel.name: lucentPM4T1E1RecvLevel
lucentPM4T1E1RecvLevel.description: An estimate of the serial interface's current recieve signal level in DB.

lucentPM4T1E1BlueAlarms.name: lucentPM4T1E1BlueAlarms
lucentPM4T1E1BlueAlarms.description: The total number of Blue Alarms on the interface.

lucentPM4T1E1YellowAlarms.name: lucentPM4T1E1YellowAlarms
lucentPM4T1E1YellowAlarms.description: The total number of Yellow Alarms on the interface.

lucentPM4T1E1CarrierLoss.name: lucentPM4T1E1CarrierLoss
lucentPM4T1E1CarrierLoss.description: The total number of times the interface has lost carrier.

lucentPM4T1E1SyncLoss.name: lucentPM4T1E1SyncLoss
lucentPM4T1E1SyncLoss.description: The total number of times the interface has lost frame synchronization.

lucentPM4T1E1BipolarErrors.name: lucentPM4T1E1BipolarErrors
lucentPM4T1E1BipolarErrors.description: The total number of bipolar violations detected on the interface.

lucentPM4T1E1CRCErrors.name: lucentPM4T1E1CRCErrors
lucentPM4T1E1CRCErrors.description: The total number of frame level CRC errors detected on the interface.

lucentPM4T1E1SyncErrors.name: lucentPM4T1E1SyncErrors
lucentPM4T1E1SyncErrors.description: The total number of frame synchronization errors detected on the interface.

lucentPM4ModemEntry.name: lucentPM4ModemEntry
lucentPM4ModemEntry.description: A modem entry containing objects at the session layer.

lucentPM4ModemBoardIndex.name: lucentPM4ModemBoardIndex
lucentPM4ModemBoardIndex.description: A unique value for each modem interface.

lucentPM4ModemUnitType.name: lucentPM4ModemUnitType
lucentPM4ModemUnitType.description: Unit type specifies the type of device or interface.

lucentPM4ModemIndex.name: lucentPM4ModemIndex
lucentPM4ModemIndex.description: A unique value for each modem interface. The value of this object can be 1 - 96 for a Quad T1, 1 - 94 for a Tri E1 card.

lucentPM4ModemPortName.name: lucentPM4ModemPortName
lucentPM4ModemPortName.description: A textual string containing the name of the serial interface (ie. S0, S1, etc).

lucentPM4ModemStatus.name: lucentPM4ModemStatus
lucentPM4ModemStatus.description: A current state of the modem.

lucentPM4ModemProtocol.name: lucentPM4ModemProtocol
lucentPM4ModemProtocol.description: The error correcting protocol being used in the modem.

lucentPM4ModemCompression.name: lucentPM4ModemCompression
lucentPM4ModemCompression.description: The compression being used in the modem interface.

lucentPM4ModemInSpeed.name: lucentPM4ModemInSpeed
lucentPM4ModemInSpeed.description: An estimate of the modem interface's current inbound bandwidth in bits per second.

lucentPM4ModemOutSpeed.name: lucentPM4ModemOutSpeed
lucentPM4ModemOutSpeed.description: An estimate of the modem interface's current outbound bandwidth in bits per second.

lucentPM4ModemInByteCount.name: lucentPM4ModemInByteCount
lucentPM4ModemInByteCount.description: The total number of bytes received on the serial interface.

lucentPM4ModemOutByteCount.name: lucentPM4ModemOutByteCount
lucentPM4ModemOutByteCount.description: The total number of bytes transmitted on the serial interface.

lucentPM4ModemRetrains.name: lucentPM4ModemRetrains
lucentPM4ModemRetrains.description: The number of retrains attempted by the modem.

lucentPM4ModemRenegotiates.name: lucentPM4ModemRenegotiates
lucentPM4ModemRenegotiates.description: The number of renegotiates attempted by the modem.

lucentPM4ModemCalls.name: lucentPM4ModemCalls
lucentPM4ModemCalls.description: The number of times a call received by the modem.

lucentPM4ModemDetects.name: lucentPM4ModemDetects
lucentPM4ModemDetects.description: The number of analog calls received by the modem.

lucentPM4ModemConnects.name: lucentPM4ModemConnects
lucentPM4ModemConnects.description: The number of successful calls received by the modem.

lucentPM4EtherTable.name: lucentPM4EtherTable
lucentPM4EtherTable.description: A list of ethernet interface entries. This object is not accessible

lucentPM4EtherEntry.name: lucentPM4EtherEntry
lucentPM4EtherEntry.description: Ethernet interface entry containing objects at the Session/Physical layers.

lucentPM4EtherBoardIndex.name: lucentPM4EtherBoardIndex
lucentPM4EtherBoardIndex.description: A unique value for each ethernet board. The manager card has two ethernet interfaces at present. The ethernet interface in slot 4 has a board ID 10 and if there is a manager card in slot 5, the board ID for the interface would be 11.

lucentPM4EtherIfType.name: lucentPM4EtherIfType
lucentPM4EtherIfType.description: The interface type which together with the board ID and the interface number will uniquely identify the interface.

lucentPM4EtherIndex.name: lucentPM4EtherIndex
lucentPM4EtherIndex.description: A unique value for each ethernet interface. The manager card has two ethernet interfaces at present. ether0(1) represents 10 Base-T interface and ether1(2) specifies the 10/100 Base-T auto-sensing ethernet interface.

lucentPM4EtherIfIndex.name: lucentPM4EtherIfIndex
lucentPM4EtherIfIndex.description: IfIndex cross reference value for the ethernet interfaces. The manager card has two ethernet interfaces at present. ether0(67436545) represents 10 Base-T interface which corresponds to board 4 and interface 1. The enumerated value ether1(168099841) specifies the 10/100 Base-T auto-sensing ethernet interface which corresponds to board 4 and interface 2. We can add the standby manager card ethernet interfaces when they are available.

lucentPM4EtherPortName.name: lucentPM4EtherPortName
lucentPM4EtherPortName.description: A printable ASCII string specifying the name of the ethernet port.

lucentPM4EtherIpGateway.name: lucentPM4EtherIpGateway
lucentPM4EtherIpGateway.description: IP address of the gateway machine.

lucentPM4EtherPriNameServer.name: lucentPM4EtherPriNameServer
lucentPM4EtherPriNameServer.description: IP address of the primary name server.

lucentPM4EtherAltNameServer.name: lucentPM4EtherAltNameServer
lucentPM4EtherAltNameServer.description: IP address of the alternate name server.

lucentPM4EtherSubnetMask.name: lucentPM4EtherSubnetMask
lucentPM4EtherSubnetMask.description: Subnet mask of the interface. Used to partition the network into different branches.

lucentPM4EtherInFilter.name: lucentPM4EtherInFilter
lucentPM4EtherInFilter.description: IP Input packet filter. Used to control the type of IP packets reaching the interface.

lucentPM4EtherOutFilter.name: lucentPM4EtherOutFilter
lucentPM4EtherOutFilter.description: IP output packet filter. Used to control the type of packets sent out of the interface.

lucentPM4EtherOptBcastHigh.name: lucentPM4EtherOptBcastHigh
lucentPM4EtherOptBcastHigh.description: Use high one(s) broadcast address enable/disable option.

lucentPM4EtherOptNoListen.name: lucentPM4EtherOptNoListen
lucentPM4EtherOptNoListen.description: Do not listen to RIP on the ether interface.

lucentPM4EtherOptPmeMsg.name: lucentPM4EtherOptPmeMsg
lucentPM4EtherOptPmeMsg.description: PME Msg. enable/disable option. Whatever that means.

lucentPM4EtherOptNoClip.name: lucentPM4EtherOptNoClip
lucentPM4EtherOptNoClip.description: No Clip enable/disable option. Whatever that means.

lucentPM4FaultMgmtChasTrap.name: lucentPM4FaultMgmtChasTrap
lucentPM4FaultMgmtChasTrap.description: Chassis Trap table which indicates one of several Traps. The chassis trap table stores the previous history of the traps which can be retrieved by the management stations at a later time. This object is not-accessible and present for MIB clarity.

lucentPM4FMChasTrapEntry.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapEntry
lucentPM4FMChasTrapEntry.description: Entry in the chassis Trap table. Each trap is uniquely identified by an index. This object is not accessible and present for MIB clarity.

lucentPM4FMChasTrapIndex.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapIndex
lucentPM4FMChasTrapIndex.description: Index into the Trap table on the agent. This table stores the previous 500 traps which can be retrieved at any given time.

lucentPM4FMChasTrapBoardID.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapBoardID
lucentPM4FMChasTrapBoardID.description: Board ID is the board number for which this trap is stored. If the trap is for an auxillary device such as a power supply or fan, this value is set to zero.

lucentPM4FMChasTrapUnitType.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapUnitType
lucentPM4FMChasTrapUnitType.description: Uniquely specifies the unit type for this trap. The unit can be a board or any other device in the chassis such as a fan or a power supply.

lucentPM4FMChasTrapUnitIndex.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapUnitIndex
lucentPM4FMChasTrapUnitIndex.description: Uniquely specifies the unit index. The unit index is same as the ifIndex for T1/E1 interfaces, or the modemIndex for the modems or fan or power supply index for fan or power supplies.

lucentPM4FMChasTrapStatus.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapStatus
lucentPM4FMChasTrapStatus.description: Trap status specifies the associated object in the Trap is online(2), offline(3), maintenance(4) or fault(5).

lucentPM4FMChasTrapSeverity.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapSeverity
lucentPM4FMChasTrapSeverity.description: Trap severity specifies the severity of the Trap for the associated object.

lucentPM4FMChasTrapTimeStamp.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapTimeStamp
lucentPM4FMChasTrapTimeStamp.description: This object stores the timestamp of this trap.

lucentPM4FMChasTrapState.name: lucentPM4FMChasTrapState
lucentPM4FMChasTrapState.description: This object stores the Trap state of this trap.

lucentPM4FMBoardIndex.name: lucentPM4FMBoardIndex
lucentPM4FMBoardIndex.description: Board index uniquely specifies the board in the chassis. This object is set to zero for power supplies, fans and other auxillary devices. This object is not accessible through Get, Get-Next or Set PDUs. It is sent out as part of the Trap.

lucentPM4FMUnitIndex.name: lucentPM4FMUnitIndex
lucentPM4FMUnitIndex.description: Unit index uniquely specifies the T1/E1 line, or modem or any device (logical/physical) in the chassis. This object is not accessible through Get, Get-Next or Set PDUs. It is sent out as part of the Trap.

lucentPM4FMUnitType.name: lucentPM4FMUnitType
lucentPM4FMUnitType.description: Unit type specifies the T1/E1 line, or modem or any device in the chassis. This object is not accessible through Get, Get-Next or Set PDUs. It is sent out as part of the Trap.

lucentPM4FMUnitTrapStatus.name: lucentPM4FMUnitTrapStatus
lucentPM4FMUnitTrapStatus.description: Trap status specifies the associated object in the Trap. This object is not accessible other than when produced as the result of a trap.

lucentPM4FMUnitTrapSeverity.name: lucentPM4FMUnitTrapSeverity
lucentPM4FMUnitTrapSeverity.description: Trap severity specifies the severity of the Trap for the associated object. This object is not accessible except when produced as the result of a trap.

lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCfg.name: lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCfg
lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCfg.description: Equipment Trap configuration table configure Traps. The objects in this table are used to enable or disable traps on a per board/interface/device basis. This object is not-accessible and present for MIB clarity.

lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCfgEntry.name: lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCfgEntry
lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCfgEntry.description: Entry in the equipment Trap config table. Each trap is uniquely identified by the board ID, Unit type and unit index. For auxillary devices such as power supplies and fans, the board index will be zero, the unit index identifies the units and the unit type specifies if the unit is a fan, power supplies etc. This object is not accessible and present for MIB clarity.

lucentPM4FMEqpBoardIndex.name: lucentPM4FMEqpBoardIndex
lucentPM4FMEqpBoardIndex.description: Board ID for which the Trap configuration need to apply. The board ID is zero if this trap configuration is for an auxillary device such as fans or power supplies.

lucentPM4FMEqpUnitType.name: lucentPM4FMEqpUnitType
lucentPM4FMEqpUnitType.description: Unit type alongwith the board index and unit index specifies uniquely the device/interface which is being configured.

lucentPM4FMEqpUnitIndex.name: lucentPM4FMEqpUnitIndex
lucentPM4FMEqpUnitIndex.description: Unit index refers to the interface or sub-device such as a modem, serial port etc. For devices such as power supplies and fans this object is zero.

lucentPM4FMEqpTrapId.name: lucentPM4FMEqpTrapId
lucentPM4FMEqpTrapId.description: Trap ID indicating the trap for which the configuration must apply.

lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCtl.name: lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCtl
lucentPM4FMEqpTrapCtl.description: Trap control which configures the trap off(1) or on(2). When the trap is configured as off(1), the trap is not sent out to the management station. When configures as on(2), the trap is sent to all the management stations configured to receive the trap.

lucentPM4FMEqpRepTimer.name: lucentPM4FMEqpRepTimer
lucentPM4FMEqpRepTimer.description: If the trap is to be repeated, this object specifies the time in seconds. When this object value is set to 0, it indicates the trap is non-repeat trap.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapCfg.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapCfg
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapCfg.description: T1/E1 Threshold Trap configuration table to configure the thresholds for various T1/E1 traps. This object is not-accessible and present for MIB clarity.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapCfgEntry.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapCfgEntry
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapCfgEntry.description: Entry in the T1/E1 threshold trap config table. Each trap is uniquely identified by the board index, unit type and unit index which is the T1/E1 interface number. This object is not accessible and present for MIB clarity.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshBoardIndex.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshBoardIndex
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshBoardIndex.description: Board ID for which the Trap threshold configuration must apply. It includes boards 1 - 10 and other devices such as power supplies and fans etc.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshUnitType.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshUnitType
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshUnitType.description: Unit type for which the Trap threshold configuration must be applied.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshESs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshESs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshESs.description: The threshold for errored seconds on the interface. A trap is issued when this set limit is exceeded. When this threshold exceeds, the performance of the interface will degrade. A trap is generated to notify the adminstrator to take appropriate action.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshSESs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshSESs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshSESs.description: The threshold for severely errored seconds on the interface. A trap is issued when this limit is exceeded. A severely errored seconds is a second with 320 or more path code violation error events or one or more out of frame defects or detected AIS defect.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshSEFSs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshSEFSs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshSEFSs.description: The threshold for severely errored framing seconds. A trap is issued when this threshold is exceeded. A severely errored framing second is a second with one or more frame defects or detected AIS defect.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshUASs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshUASs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshUASs.description: The threshold for unavailable seconds. A trap is issued when this set threshold is exceeded. Unavailable seconds are calculated by counting the number of seconds that the interface is unavailable from the onset of 10 SESs. Once unavailable, the interface becomes available at the onset of 10 contiguous no SESs.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshCSSs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshCSSs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshCSSs.description: The threshold for controlled slip seconds on the interface. A trap is issued when this set threshold is exceeded. A controlled slip second is a one-second interval containing one or more controlled slips.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshPCVs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshPCVs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshPCVs.description: The threshold for path code violations on the interface. A trap is issued when this set threshold is exceeded. PCV is a frame syncronization bit error in the D4 and E1-noCRC format interfaces or a CRC error in the ESF (extended super frame) and E1-CRC interface formats.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshLESs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshLESs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshLESs.description: The threshold for line errored seconds on the interface. A trap is sent to the manager when this set threshold is exceeded. A line errored second, according to T1M1.3 is a second in which one or more line code violations were detected.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshBESs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshBESs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshBESs.description: The threshold for bursty errored seconds on the interface. A trap is sent to the manager when this set threshold is exceeded. A bursty errored second is a second with fewer than 320 and more than 1 path code violations.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshDMs.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshDMs
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshDMs.description: The threshold for degraded minutes on the interface. A trap is sent to the manager when this set threshold is exceeded. Degraded minutes are determined by collecting all of the available seconds, after removing any severely errored seconds. The resulting seconds is grouped into 60 second intervals and if the cumulative errors during the seconds present in the group exceeds 1E-6.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshRepTimer.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshRepTimer
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshRepTimer.description: If the trap is to be repeated, this object specifies the time in seconds. When this object value is set to 0, it indicates the trap is non-repeat trap.

lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapAck.name: lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapAck
lucentPM4FMT1E1ThreshTrapAck.description: If set to ack(3), clears the trap condition. If the value is set to noack(2), leaves the trap condition unchanged.

lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCfg.name: lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCfg
lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCfg.description: Environment Trap configuration table. This table enables configuration of voltage, power levels and temperature ranges for different units in the chassis. This object is not-accessible and present for MIB clarity.

lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCfgEntry.name: lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCfgEntry
lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCfgEntry.description: Entry in the environment trap config table. Each trap is uniquely identified by the board index, unit type and unit index. This object is not accessible and present for MIB clarity.

lucentPM4FMEnvBoardID.name: lucentPM4FMEnvBoardID
lucentPM4FMEnvBoardID.description: Board ID specifies the board identifier for this trap. If the trap configuration is for an auxillary device such as a power supply or fan, this object will be set to zero. The unit type and the unit index will uniquely identify the auxillary devices.

lucentPM4FMEnvUnitType.name: lucentPM4FMEnvUnitType
lucentPM4FMEnvUnitType.description: Unit for which the Trap configuration must to apply.

lucentPM4FMEnvUnitIndex.name: lucentPM4FMEnvUnitIndex
lucentPM4FMEnvUnitIndex.description: Unit index specifies the interface or sub-unit for this trap (modem or T1/E1 interface etc.). The unit type and the unit index will uniquely identify the auxillary devices.

lucentPM4FMEnvOptUnitTemp.name: lucentPM4FMEnvOptUnitTemp
lucentPM4FMEnvOptUnitTemp.description: The optimum temperature for this unit. A trap is generated when the temperature deviates from the specified range. The temperature is specified as an integer in degrees farenheit.

lucentPM4FMEnvUnitTempRange.name: lucentPM4FMEnvUnitTempRange
lucentPM4FMEnvUnitTempRange.description: The temperature range above which a trap is generated. The temperature must be specified as an integer in degree Farenhiet (for example +/- 5 degree Far.).

lucentPM4FMEnvOptUnitPwrLvl.name: lucentPM4FMEnvOptUnitPwrLvl
lucentPM4FMEnvOptUnitPwrLvl.description: The optimal power level that is appropriate for this unit. A trap is generated when the power level fluctuates outside the limits set.

lucentPM4FMEnvUnitPwrRange.name: lucentPM4FMEnvUnitPwrRange
lucentPM4FMEnvUnitPwrRange.description: The power range specified in volts. A trap is generated when the power level fluctuates outside the Opt Pwr +/- Range set.

lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCtl.name: lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCtl
lucentPM4FMEnvTrapCtl.description: The trap control used to turn the environment traps on or off for the specified unit(s).

lucentPM4T1E1PMCur.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCur
lucentPM4T1E1PMCur.description: Performance management table representing the performance statistics of T1/E1 interfaces in the box. This table represents the current 15 mins statistics. This object is not accessible and present for clarity purpose. This table is part of RFC 1406.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurEntry.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurEntry
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurEntry.description: Performance management table entries for all the T1/E1 interfaces in the box. This table represents the current 15 mins statistics. This object is not accessible and present for clarity purpose.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurBoard.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurBoard
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurBoard.description: Board number of the interface. The global interface number is computed by using the Most Significant byte of the ifIndex and the Least Significant 2 bytes represents the interface index. Byte 3 will represent the unit type which would be a T1 or E1.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurUnitType.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurUnitType
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurUnitType.description: Unit type indicates the type of interface as T1/E1 or T3/E3 in future. This is part of the interface table ifIndex which is constructed with boardID, unit type and unit index.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLineNum.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLineNum
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLineNum.description: Line number uniquely identifies the T1/E1 interface on a given board.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurIfIndex.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurIfIndex
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurIfIndex.description: Interface table ifIndex cross reference. The global interface number is computed by using the Most Significant byte as the board ID and the Least Significant 2 bytes represents the interface index. The third byte represents the unit type which will be a T1 or E1. Thus board 0 interface 3 is represented as 0x00050003. The global interface number corresponds to the IfIndex in MIB II.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurESs.description: The number of errored seconds, encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurSESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurSESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurSEFSs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurSEFSs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurUASs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurUASs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurCSSs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurCSSs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurPCVs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurPCVs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurPCVs.description: The number of Path Coding Violations encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLESs.description: The number of Line Errored Seconds encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurBESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurBESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurDMs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurDMs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurDMs.description: The number of Degraded Minutes encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLCVs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLCVs
lucentPM4T1E1PMCurLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations encountered by the line in the current 15 mins interval.

lucentPM4T1E1PMInt.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMInt
lucentPM4T1E1PMInt.description: Performance management table representing the performance statistics of T1/E1 interfaces in the box. This table represents the 24 hr statistics divided into 96 15 mins intervals. This object is not accessible and present for clarity purpose. This table is part of RFC 1406.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntEntry.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntEntry
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntEntry.description: Performance management table entries for all the T1/E1 interfaces in the box. This table represents the 24 hr statistics divided into 96 15 mins intervals. This object is not accessible and present for clarity purpose.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntBoard.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntBoard
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntBoard.description: Board number of the interface. The global interface number is computed by using the Most Significant nibble of the ifIndex and the Least Significant nibble represents the interface index. Thus board 0 interface 3 is represented as 0x03 or 03 decimal and board 10 interface 3 is represented as 0xa3 or 163 decimal. In an integer, of 4 bytes wide, the 3 MSBytes will all be zeros. The global interface number corresponds to the IfIndex of MIB II.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntUnitType.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntUnitType
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntUnitType.description: Unit type indicates the type of physical or logical device. The unit type for this table is either T1 or E1.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLineNum.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLineNum
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLineNum.description: Line number uniquely identifies the T1/E1 interface for this board.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntInterval.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntInterval
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntInterval.description: Interval number for a given board. The 24 hr period is divided into 96 15 min intervals, where 1 is the most recent and 96 is the least recent.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntIfIndex.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntIfIndex
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntIfIndex.description: Interface table ifIndex cross reference. The global interface number is computed by using the Most Significant byte as the board ID and the Least Significant 2 bytes represents the interface index. The third byte represents the unit type which will be a T1 or E1. Thus board 0 interface 3 is represented as 0x00050003. The global interface number corresponds to the IfIndex in MIB II.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntESs.description: The number of errored seconds, encountered by the line in the last 24 hrs divided into 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntSESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntSESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntSEFSs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntSEFSs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntUASs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntUASs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntCSSs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntCSSs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntPCVs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntPCVs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntPCVs.description: The number of Path Coding Violations encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLESs.description: The number of Line Errored Seconds encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntBESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntBESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntDMs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntDMs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntDMs.description: The number of Degraded Minutes encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLCVs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLCVs
lucentPM4T1E1PMIntLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations encountered by the line for one of the 96 15 mins intervals.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotal.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotal
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotal.description: Performance management table representing the performance statistics of T1/E1 interfaces in the box. This table represents the 24 hr statistics divided into 96 15 mins intervals. This object is not accessible and present for clarity purpose. This table is part of RFC 1406.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalEntry.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalEntry
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalEntry.description: Performance management table entries for all the T1/E1 interfaces in the box. This table represents the 24 hr statistics divided into 96 15 mins intervals. This object is not accessible and present for clarity purpose.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalBoard.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalBoard
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalBoard.description: Board number of the interface. The global interface number is computed by using the Most Significant nibble of the ifIndex and the Least Significant nibble represents the interface index. Thus board 0 interface 3 is represented as 0x03 or 03 decimal and board 10 interface 3 is represented as 0xa3 or 163 decimal. In an integer, of 4 bytes wide, the 3 MSBytes will all be zeros. The global interface number corresponds to the IfIndex of MIB II. This table stores the cumulative values for the past 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalUnitType.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalUnitType
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalUnitType.description: Unit type indicates the type of physical or logical device. The unit type for this table is either T1 or E1.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLineNum.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLineNum
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLineNum.description: Interface number for a given board. The global interface number is computed by using the Most Significant nibble of the ifIndex and the Least Significant nibble represents the interface index. Thus board 0 interface 3 is represented as 0x03 or 03 decimal and board 10 interface 3 is represented as 0xa3 or 163 decimal. In an integer, of 4 bytes wide, the 3 MSBytes will all be zeros. The global interface number corresponds to the IfIndex in MIB II.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalIfIndex.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalIfIndex
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalIfIndex.description: IfIndex cross reference value. This value is obtained from the Board/board number and interface number by combining them into the LSByte. The upper nibble represents the board and the lower nibble represents the line number.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalESs.description: The cumulative value of errored seconds, encountered by the line in the last 24 hrs.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalSESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalSESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalSESs.description: The cumulative value Severely Errored Seconds encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalSEFSs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalSEFSs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalSEFSs.description: The cumulative value of Severely Errored Framing Seconds encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalUASs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalUASs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalUASs.description: The cumulative value of Unavailable Seconds encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalCSSs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalCSSs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalCSSs.description: The cumulative value of Controlled Slip Seconds encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalPCVs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalPCVs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalPCVs.description: The cumulative value of Path Coding Violations encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLESs.description: The cumulative value of Line Errored Seconds encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalBESs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalBESs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalBESs.description: The cumulative value of Bursty Errored Seconds encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalDMs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalDMs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalDMs.description: The cumulative value of Degraded Minutes encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLCVs.name: lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLCVs
lucentPM4T1E1PMTotalLCVs.description: The cumulative value of Line Code Violations encountered by the line for the 24 hr period.

lucentPM4SnmpCommTable.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommTable
lucentPM4SnmpCommTable.description: The SNMP Community Table. This table contains entries to restrict the SNMP get and set operations.

lucentPM4SnmpCommEntry.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommEntry
lucentPM4SnmpCommEntry.description: The entries in the community table.

lucentPM4SnmpCommIndex.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommIndex
lucentPM4SnmpCommIndex.description: The index of the command in the command table. A MAX of 10 network management stations must be specified along with their community names.

lucentPM4SnmpCommName.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommName
lucentPM4SnmpCommName.description: The name of the SNMP Community for SNMP readers and writers. The size of the string is limited to 32 characters. All characters in the string must be printable.

lucentPM4SnmpCommIpAddr.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommIpAddr
lucentPM4SnmpCommIpAddr.description: The IP Address of the remote community.

lucentPM4SnmpCommReadAccess.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommReadAccess
lucentPM4SnmpCommReadAccess.description: Read access enable or disable for this community. When enabled, it allows read-only variable access using this community string by the SNMP client.

lucentPM4SnmpCommWriteAccess.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommWriteAccess
lucentPM4SnmpCommWriteAccess.description: Write access enable or disable for this community. When enabled, the agent allows write access to the parameters on the agent by the SNMP clients.

lucentPM4SnmpCommTraps.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommTraps
lucentPM4SnmpCommTraps.description: Traps receiving capability enable or disable for this community. When enabled, the SNMP agent forwards the traps generated in the box to this SNMP client.

lucentPM4SnmpCommStatus.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommStatus
lucentPM4SnmpCommStatus.description: The status of the entry for this community. If the status is set to normal, it allows requests from this SNMP client else it discards the requests from this client.

lucentPM4SnmpCommLastError.name: lucentPM4SnmpCommLastError
lucentPM4SnmpCommLastError.description: If there is an error on a request, this variable may contain a message indicating the error.

lucentPM4AMCallEventTable.name: lucentPM4AMCallEventTable
lucentPM4AMCallEventTable.description: Call accounting table containing a list of call events, which may be used for billing purposes.

lucentPM4AMCallEventEntry.name: lucentPM4AMCallEventEntry
lucentPM4AMCallEventEntry.description: The entries in the accounting/billing table.

lucentPM4AMCEIndex.name: lucentPM4AMCEIndex
lucentPM4AMCEIndex.description: Call event index used as an index into the call event table. The table stores call events which may be used for billing.

lucentPM4AMCETimeStamp.name: lucentPM4AMCETimeStamp
lucentPM4AMCETimeStamp.description: Time stamp for this event in seconds since the last reboot.

lucentPM4AMCEType.name: lucentPM4AMCEType
lucentPM4AMCEType.description: Specifies the type of event associated with this entry in the call event table.

lucentPM4AMCESvcType.name: lucentPM4AMCESvcType
lucentPM4AMCESvcType.description: The type of service provided to the user. This field is meaningful if the event type is servicechanged(4), or namechanged(5) events. In all other cases, this object must return none(1).

lucentPM4AMCEUName.name: lucentPM4AMCEUName
lucentPM4AMCEUName.description: User name of the dialed in user. This object returns the valid user name when the event type is servicechanged(4) or namechanged(5). In all other cases, it returns a NULL.

lucentPM4AMCEModemBoard.name: lucentPM4AMCEModemBoard
lucentPM4AMCEModemBoard.description: Board ID of the modem which handled this call. This value can be used to diagnose modem related problems (dropping the call, retraining too frequently etc.).

lucentPM4AMCEModemID.name: lucentPM4AMCEModemID
lucentPM4AMCEModemID.description: Identifies the specific modem on a board which handled this call. Can be used to diagnose modem related problems.

lucentPM4AMCEModemPort.name: lucentPM4AMCEModemPort
lucentPM4AMCEModemPort.description: A textual string containing the name of the serial interface (ie. S0, S1, etc).

lucentPM4AMCEDataRate.name: lucentPM4AMCEDataRate
lucentPM4AMCEDataRate.description: Specifies the speed of this connection. Speed is specified as baud rate for modem calls and receive data rate for ISDN calls. This object returns a 0 for call answered and call cleared events.

lucentPM4AMCECallingPartyID.name: lucentPM4AMCECallingPartyID
lucentPM4AMCECallingPartyID.description: Calling party ID. This object is valid only for call answered, call originated, and call cleared events. For all invalid event types, this object is set to NULL.

lucentPM4AMCECalledPartyID.name: lucentPM4AMCECalledPartyID
lucentPM4AMCECalledPartyID.description: Called party ID. This object is valid only for call answered, call originated, and call cleared events. For all invalid event types, this object is set to NULL.

lucentPM4AMCEInOctets.name: lucentPM4AMCEInOctets
lucentPM4AMCEInOctets.description: Total octets received during this call. This object is cleared at the end of each call.

lucentPM4AMCEOutOctets.name: lucentPM4AMCEOutOctets
lucentPM4AMCEOutOctets.description: Total octets sent out during this call. This object is cleared at the end of each call.

lucentPM4AMCECallCharge.name: lucentPM4AMCECallCharge
lucentPM4AMCECallCharge.description: Call charge for this call. This object is valid only when the event is call cleared. For all other events this object is set to zero.

lucentPM4BoardOfflineTrap.name: lucentPM4BoardOfflineTrap
lucentPM4BoardOfflineTrap.description: Board down trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, board number and the trap status. This Trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4BoardOnlineTrap.name: lucentPM4BoardOnlineTrap
lucentPM4BoardOnlineTrap.description: Board up trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, board number and the trap status. This Trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4PwrSupFailTrap.name: lucentPM4PwrSupFailTrap
lucentPM4PwrSupFailTrap.description: Power supply failed trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, power supply unit and the trap status. This Trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4PwrSupWarnTrap.name: lucentPM4PwrSupWarnTrap
lucentPM4PwrSupWarnTrap.description: Power supply warning trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, power supply unit and the trap status. This Trap is issued when the power supply fluctuates between a set threshold. This Trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4PwrSupRestoredTrap.name: lucentPM4PwrSupRestoredTrap
lucentPM4PwrSupRestoredTrap.description: Power supply restored trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, power supply unit and the trap status. This Trap is issued when a failed power supply is restored. This must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4FanFailTrap.name: lucentPM4FanFailTrap
lucentPM4FanFailTrap.description: Fan failure trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, fan number and the trap status. This Trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4FanRestoredTrap.name: lucentPM4FanRestoredTrap
lucentPM4FanRestoredTrap.description: Fan restored trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, fan number and the trap status. This Trap is issued when the failed fan is restored. This trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4BoardTempWarnTrap.name: lucentPM4BoardTempWarnTrap
lucentPM4BoardTempWarnTrap.description: Board temperature warning trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, unit and the trap status. This Trap is issued when the board temperature exceeds a set threshold value. This trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4BoardTempNormalTrap.name: lucentPM4BoardTempNormalTrap
lucentPM4BoardTempNormalTrap.description: Board temperature normal trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, unit and the trap status. This Trap is issued when the board temperature returns to normal. This trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4BoardTooHotTrap.name: lucentPM4BoardTooHotTrap
lucentPM4BoardTooHotTrap.description: Board trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, board number and the trap status. This Trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4ModemFailTrap.name: lucentPM4ModemFailTrap
lucentPM4ModemFailTrap.description: Modem failure trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, modem number and the trap status. This Trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4T1E1LineDownTrap.name: lucentPM4T1E1LineDownTrap
lucentPM4T1E1LineDownTrap.description: T1/E1 Line trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide all the information for the clients to display the Board ID, Line ID and the status of the line. This Trap could be generated when the line comes up or goes down once. It must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4T1E1LineUpTrap.name: lucentPM4T1E1LineUpTrap
lucentPM4T1E1LineUpTrap.description: T1/E1 Line trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide all the information for the clients to display the Board ID, Line ID and the status of the line. This Trap could be generated when the line comes up or goes down once. It must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4T1E1LineThreshTrap.name: lucentPM4T1E1LineThreshTrap
lucentPM4T1E1LineThreshTrap.description: T1/E1 Line trap. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide all the information for the clients to display the Board ID, Line ID and the trap type. This Trap could be generated when the thresholds for the various performance statistics (ES, SES etc.) exceed. It must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4BoardPwrOffTrap.name: lucentPM4BoardPwrOffTrap
lucentPM4BoardPwrOffTrap.description: This trap is issued when the power supply to the board is not enough. The variable bindings in the Trap packet provide information about the chassis name, board/board number and the trap status. This Trap must be cleared manually.

lucentPM4RadiusAuthFailTrap.name: lucentPM4RadiusAuthFailTrap
lucentPM4RadiusAuthFailTrap.description: This trap is issued when the Radius authentication fails. This Trap must be cleared manually. The trap provides information about the board and the modem number.
